ds/2022/02/Easy-Cream-Cheese-Frosting.jpg"><noscript><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="1800" src="https://valentinascorner.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Easy-Cream-Cheese-Frosting.jpg" alt="A whisk with cream cheese frosting on it. " class="wp-image-320153" title="An easy cream cheese frosting is exactly what these shortcake cupcakes with strawberries need. " data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="" data-jpibfi-post-url="https://valentinascorner.com/strawberry-shortcake-cupcakes/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Strawberry Shortcake Cupcakes" data-jpibfi-src="https://valentinascorner.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Easy-Cream-Cheese-Frosting.jpg" srcset="https://valentinascorner.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Easy-Cream-Cheese-Frosting.jpg 1200w, https://valentinascorner.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Easy-Cream-Cheese-Frosting-450x675.jpg 450w, https://valentinascorner.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Easy-Cream-Cheese-Frosting-760x1140.jpg 760w, https://valentinascorner.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Easy-Cream-Cheese-Frosting-100x150.jpg 100w, https://valentinascorner.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Easy-Cream-Cheese-Frosting-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://valentinascorner.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Easy-Cream-Cheese-Frosting-270x405.jpg 270w, https://valentinascorner.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Easy-Cream-Cheese-Frosting-226x339.jpg 226w, https://valentinascorner.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Easy-Cream-Cheese-Frosting-54x81.jpg 54w, https://valentinascorner.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Easy-Cream-Cheese-Frosting-108x162.jpg 108w, https://valentinascorner.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Easy-Cream-Cheese-Frosting-360x540.jpg 360w, https://valentinascorner.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Easy-Cream-Cheese-Frosting-540x810.jpg 540w, https://valentinascorner.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Easy-Cream-Cheese-Frosting-720x1080.jpg 720w" sizes="(max-width: 800px) calc(100vw - 40px), 760px"></noscript></figure>



<p>2 &ndash; <strong>Make the frosting:&nbsp;</strong>In an electric mixer using the whisk attachment, cream together cream cheese and butter on medium speed. Add in vanilla extract and powdered sugar and beat until light &amp; fluffy.&nbsp;</p>
</div>
</div>
</div></div>


