<div class="customheading customheading-pink customheading-dark"><h2 class="ch-heading"><svg class="cicon icon-lightbulb" aria-hidden="true"><use xlink:href="#icon-lightbulb"></use></svg><span>Expert Tips for Making the Perfect Cupcakes:</span></h2><div class="customheading-inner notop nobot">
<ul class="wp-block-list is-style-check">
<li><strong>Have the right tools: </strong>You can use an electric stand mixer or even a hand mixer to make the cupcake batter and the frosting.</li>



<li><strong>Baking the cupcakes: </strong>Use a cupcake pan or a muffin tin to bake your cupcakes. Be&nbsp; sure to line the pan with paper liners before adding the cupcake mixture.</li>



<li><strong>Proper bake time!</strong> Don&rsquo;t overbake the cupcakes! Check their doneness at 16 minutes with a toothpick.&nbsp;</li>



<li><strong>Cool.</strong> Let the cupcakes cool before filling and frosting them!</li>



<li><strong>Keep refrigerated.</strong> Keep the cupcake frosting in the fridge before you are ready to pipe. Since the frosting is made of cream cheese and butter, the frosting can melt quickly.&nbsp;</li>



<li><strong>Piping tip.</strong> Use a <a href="https://amzn.to/3MQ1Hye" rel="nofollow sponsored noopener" target="_blank">piping bag and frosting tips</a> to make the perfect cupcake.</li>
</ul>
</div></div>

<div class="customheading customheading-pink customheading-light"><h2 class="ch-heading"><svg class="cicon icon-question" aria-hidden="true"><use xlink:href="#icon-question"></use></svg><span>Recipe FAQs</span></h2><div class="customheading-inner notop nobot">
<div class="schema-faq wp-block-yoast-faq-block"><div class="schema-faq-section" id="faq-question-1711736816056"><strong class="schema-faq-question"><strong>Can frozen strawberries be used for this recipe?</strong></strong> <p class="schema-faq-answer">We recommend only using fresh strawberries, as frozen strawberries will release too much moisture.&nbsp;</p> </div> <div class="schema-faq-section" id="faq-question-1711736848846"><strong class="schema-faq-question"><strong>Am I able to use a boxed cake mix?&nbsp;</strong></strong> <p class="schema-faq-answer">Make this recipe even easier by using a boxed cake mix!</p> </div> <div class="schema-faq-section" id="faq-question-1711736861529"><strong class="schema-faq-question"><strong>Is there a different frosting I can use?&nbsp;</strong></strong> <p class="schema-faq-answer">You can use a vanilla whipped cream frosting or even a cheesecake frosting.&nbsp;</p> </div> <div class="schema-faq-section" id="faq-question-1711736872525"><strong class="schema-faq-question"><strong>What can I substitute for strawberry jelly?</strong></strong> <p class="schema-faq-answer">You can use a strawberry jam or make your own strawberry jam.</p> </div> </div>
</div></div>


<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="1200" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201200%201200'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="A strawberry shortcake cupcake sliced in half to show the strawberry filling inside of the cupcake. " class="wp-image-336069" title="There's nothing like an easy cupcake recipe, and these strawberry shortcake cupcakes are it! " data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="" data-jpibfi-post-url="https://valentinascorner.com/strawberry-shortcake-cupcakes/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Strawberry Shortcake Cupcakes" data-jpibfi-src="https://valentinascorner.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Easy-Strawberry-Shortcake-Cupcakes-1.jpg" data-lazy-srcset="https://valentinascorner.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Easy-Strawberry-Shortcake-Cupcakes-1.jpg 1200w, https://valentinascorner.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Easy-Strawberry-Shortcake-Cupcakes-1-450x450.jpg 450w, https://valentinascorner.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Easy-Strawberry-Shortcake-Cupcakes-1-760x760.jpg 760w, https://valentinascorner.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Easy-Strawberry-Shortcake-Cupcakes-1-150x150.jpg 150w, https://valentinascorner.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Easy-Strawberry-Shortcake-Cupcakes-1-500x500.jpg 500w, https://valentinascorner.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Easy-Strawberry-Shortcake-Cupcakes-1-96x96.jpg 96w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 800px) calc(100vw - 40px), 760px" data-lazy-src="https://valentinascorner.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Easy-Strawberry-Shortcake-Cupcakes-1.jpg"><noscript><img decoding="async" width="1200" height="1200" src="https://valentinascorner.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Easy-Strawberry-Shortcake-Cupcakes-1.jpg" alt="A strawberry shortcake cupcake sliced in half to show the strawberry filling inside of the cupcake. " class="wp-image-336069" title="There's nothing like an easy cupcake recipe, and these strawberry shortcake cupcakes are it! " data-jpibfi-post-excerpt="" data-jpibfi-post-url="https://valentinascorner.com/strawberry-shortcake-cupcakes/" data-jpibfi-post-title="Strawberry Shortcake Cupcakes" data-jpibfi-src="https://valentinascorner.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Easy-Strawberry-Shortcake-Cupcakes-1.jpg" srcset="https://valentinascorner.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Easy-Strawberry-Shortcake-Cupcakes-1.jpg 1200w, https://valentinascorner.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Easy-Strawberry-Shortcake-Cupcakes-1-450x450.jpg 450w, https://valentinascorner.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Easy-Strawberry-Shortcake-Cupcakes-1-760x760.jpg 760w, https://valentinascorner.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Easy-Strawberry-Shortcake-Cupcakes-1-150x150.jpg 150w, https://valentinascorner.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Easy-Strawberry-Shortcake-Cupcakes-1-500x500.jpg 500w, https://valentinascorner.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Easy-Strawberry-Shortcake-Cupcakes-1-96x96.jpg 96w" sizes="(max-width: 800px) calc(100vw - 40px), 760px"></noscript></figure>



<div class="wp-block-group"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"><div class="customheading customheading-pink customheading-dark"><h2 class="ch-heading"><svg class="cicon icon-refrigerator" aria-hidden="true"><use xlink:href="#icon-refrigerator"></use></svg><span><strong>Store &amp; Reheat</strong></span></h2><div class="customheading-inner notop nobot">
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Storage.&nbsp;</strong>Keep leftover cupcakes in the fridge, in an airtight container for up to 3 days.&nbsp;</li>



<li><strong>Freeze.&nbsp;</strong>If you plan on freezing the cupcakes, arrange the unfrosted cupcakes in a freezer-safe bag or container. Freeze for up to 3 months. Thaw: Take the cupcakes out of the freezer and allow them to thaw at room temperature. You can frost them before they are fully thawed.</li>
</ul>
</div></div></div></div>


<div class="customheading customheading-grey customheading-light"><h2 class="ch-heading"><span><strong>More Dessert Recipes</strong></span></h2><div class="customheading-inner notop nobot">
<p>If you enjoyed this strawberry cupcake recipe, be sure to try our other&nbsp;<a href="https://valentinascorner.com/category/recipes/desserts/">popular dessert recipes</a>, here are some of our favorite:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
